snippet.textDisplay:
Drake, drake, drake.
One talented man. He knows exactly how to satisfy his fans..
I watched his rapradar interview before listening to this. So I saw he was excited about this drop, the content in the lyrics and how he's spit it. He mentioned in the interview that enjoys listening to UK drill. I'm from the UK and I love that he's INSPIRED by the music here. No one can't deny that he hasn't given UK artists more exposure. Props to him, don't be hating that you can hear the inspiration in his music.
We're all inspired by other artists music, culture, stories, background , religion etc.
So instead praise the man for continuing to keep it relevant!
We see you drake!
On another note. Please watch Lost in Vegas reaction to this song. They got the grime genre wrong but they're speaking truth. Also their comment section is a good read. All of their reactions on hip hop music is unbiased, informative and sometimes funny!
